content: A missile strike on the al-Ahli hospital in Gaza has killed at least 500, according to local authorities. Palestinian Authority, Hamas, and Egypt all say it was an Israeli airstrike. Israel isn't confirming that, says they're investigating but that they warned the hospital to evacuate days ago. (Bombing hospitals is against international law, regardless of the warnings.)

content:
Having told people to evacuate from northern Gaza to the south, Israel has since bombed the southern cities of Khan Younis and Rafah. Earlier today they also bombed a UNRWA school in the al-Maghazi Refugee Camp which is also south of the area identified for evacuation. And now news is breaking of the bombing of Al Ahli Arab hospital in Gaza City with hundreds dead.

Since 7th October, over 3,000 people have been killed on Gaza and a further 12,500 injured and rising.
